    "Management": {
      "text": "Symptomatic therapies are the mainstay of treatment\nAntiemetics\nand\nIVF\nAtropine\nfor bradycardia\nMannitol\n- Recommended by several experts for neurologic symptoms if given within 24-48 hours of onset\n[1]\n. However, no benefit over normal saline in RCT\n[2]\nCaution: patients may be hypovolemic due to vomiting/diarrhea and should be appropriately volume resuscitated prior to considering mannitol\nAmitriptyline\nreported effective for neuropathic pain in several case series\n[3]\n[4]\nGabapentin\n[5]\nand\nPregabalin\n[6]\nalso reported to control neurologic symptoms\nPrevent recurrences - instruct patient to not ingest alcohol, caffeine, nuts or fish for 6 months",
